source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1974, 1992, 2022 censuses; (b) adjusted for age heaping; (c) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (d) official estimates through 2022; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration.  Note: The 2004 and 2010 censuses have also been considered.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2022; (b) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2009; (c) birth-histories data from the 1987 CHS and 1996-1997 FHS; (d) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1999, 2000, 2007 DS and 2004, 2022 censuses; (e) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1974, 1992, 2004, 2022 censuses and 2016 DS; (f) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1996-1997 FHS and 1999, 2007 DS. In addition, the (a) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 2016, 2017 DS and 2018 HHS and 2019 WHS; (b) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1964-2011 Education Stats have been considered.  Note: Excluded 2010 census based on GAStat assessment that this census was unreliable.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) official estimates through 2022; (b) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2022; (c) adjusted for underregistration; (d) adjusted for underreporting of infant and child deaths; (e) mortality rates for older ages were adjusted.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 1990-2022 Estimates and 2004, 2010 censuses and 2007, 2016 DS; (b) recent household deaths adjusted at adult ages for underregistration using death distribution methods; (c) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions; (d) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the (a) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1987 CHS and 1996-1997 FHS and 2004, 2010 censuses and 2007, 2016, 2017 DS; (b) indirect estimates of female adult mortality based on male widowhood data from the 1987 CHS and 1996-1997 FHS and 2007, 2016, 2017 DS and 2010 Census have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) official estimates of infant and child mortality through 2022; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2016, 2017 DS and 2018 HHS; (c) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1987 CHS and 1996-1997 FHS; (d) recent household deaths from the 1999, 2000, 2007, 2016, 2017 DS and 2004 Census and 2018 HHS; (e) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the (a) registered infant and child deaths through 2022; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1996-1997 FHS and 2004 Census have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
